{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2020/01/06/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"fffaraz/awesome-cpp","categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://lame.sourceforge.io/using.php\">LAME</a> - LAME is a high quality MPEG Audio Layer III (MP3) encoder. [LGPL]</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T23:54:39.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>How To Use</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>If you get stuck, find an online community and <a href=\"http://www.catb.org/esr/faqs/smart-questions.html\">ask smart questions</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Lisp Environments</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>Prepackaged environments\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://shinmera.github.io/portacle/\">Portacle</a> - A portable and multiplatform Common Lisp environment. It ships a slightly customized Emacs with SLIME, SBCL (a popular Common Lisp implementation), Quicklisp and Git. No installation needed, so it's a very quick and easy way to get going.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://common-lisp.net/project/lispbox/\">Lispbox</a> - An IDE (Emacs + SLIME), Common Lisp implementation (Clozure Common Lisp) and library manager (Quicklisp), pre-packaged as archives for Windows, macOS and Linux. Descendant of \"Lisp in a Box\" <a href=\"http://www.gigamonkeys.com/book/lather-rinse-repeat-a-tour-of-the-repl.html\">mentioned</a> in Practical Common Lisp.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.lispworks.com/downloads/\">Lispworks Personal Edition</a> - A non-Emacs based IDE for LispWorks Lisp, with some restrictions.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://franz.com/products/allegrocl/\">Allegro Common Lisp</a> - Has a free <a href=\"https://franz.com/downloads/clp/survey\">Express Edition</a> IDE, and <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCN36UrxtyNBJPaG0kmBJNRw\">training videos on YouTube</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Lisp Environments</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>For advanced users\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://articulate-lisp.com\">Articulate Common Lisp</a> - A HOWTO for putting together a Lisp environment, and has information on <a href=\"http://articulate-lisp.com/project/abcs.html\">useful libraries</a> and how to <a href=\"http://articulate-lisp.com/project/new-project.html\">structure projects</a>.</li>\n<li>If you're an experienced <a href=\"https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/\">Emacs</a> user, you can just install <a href=\"https://common-lisp.net/project/slime/\">SLIME</a> and a <a href=\"https://common-lisp.net/project/slime/doc/html/Platforms.html#Platforms\">supported Common Lisp implementation</a>. See the <a href=\"https://common-lisp.net/project/slime/doc/html/\">SLIME manual</a> for more details.</li>\n<li>The Common Lisp Cookbook has more information about <a href=\"https://lispcookbook.github.io/cl-cookbook/getting-started.html\">installing an implementation</a> using an implementation manager like <a href=\"https://github.com/roswell/roswell/wiki\">Roswell</a>, or on Docker.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online References</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://lispcookbook.github.io/cl-cookbook/\">The Common Lisp Cookbook</a> - A list of useful Lisp recipes. Also contains a list of other online sources of CL information.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online References</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.cmu.edu/Groups/AI/html/cltl/cltl2.html\">Common Lisp the Language (2nd Edition) by Guy L. Steele</a> - A description of the Common Lisp language from just before it was standardized by ANSI. Don't use it as a reference.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://cliki.net/Getting+Started\">Cliki on CLtL2</a> - Claims it has more useful descriptions of <a href=\"http://www.cs.cmu.edu/afs/cs.cmu.edu/project/ai-repository/ai/html/cltl/clm/node235.html#SECTION003000000000000000000\">LOOP</a> and <a href=\"http://www.cs.cmu.edu/afs/cs.cmu.edu/project/ai-repository/ai/html/cltl/clm/node200.html\">FORMAT</a> than the CLHS does.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/108537/what-are-the-main-differences-between-cltl2-and-ansi-cl\">Stack Overflow on CLtL2</a> - Some recommend using CLtL2 for insight and inspiration, but to use the CLHS when programming.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://linuxfinances.info/info/commonlisp.html#AEN9679\">A list of differences between CLtL2 and the ANSI Common Lisp specification.</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.cmu.edu/Groups/AI/html/cltl/clm/node260.html#SECTION003200000000000000000\">Chapter 28</a> - Covers the Common Lisp Object System.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~dst/LispBook/\">Common Lisp: A Gentle Introduction to Symbolic Computation by David S. Touretzky</a> - a good introduction for people new to programming. Contains code for really useful utilities like <a href=\"http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~dst/Lisp/dtrace/\">DTRACE</a> and <a href=\"http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~dst/Lisp/sdraw/\">SDRAW</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cse.buffalo.edu/~shapiro/Commonlisp/\">Common Lisp: An interactive approach by Stuart C. Shapiro</a> - A textbook that teaches mainly through the use of exercises.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.gigamonkeys.com/book/\">Practical Common Lisp by Peter Seibel</a> - A great introduction for experienced programmers, and tries to highlight from the very beginning what makes CL different to other languages.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/google/lisp-koans\">Common Lisp Koans</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/google/lisp-koans\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.8k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2816,\"repo\":\"google/lisp-koans\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Not exactly a book, but a set of koans to help you learn the language.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.paulgraham.com/onlisp.html\">On Lisp by Paul Graham</a> - A great book for intermediately experienced Lispers.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/norvig/paip-lisp\">Paradigms of Artificial Intelligence Programming by Peter Norvig</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/norvig/paip-lisp\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.6k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5556,\"repo\":\"norvig/paip-lisp\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Has many interesting applications of Lisp, but is no longer a good reference for AI.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Offline Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.paulgraham.com/acl.html\">ANSI Common Lisp by Paul Graham</a> - Good as a reference, covers CLOS, and has several example program implementations.\n<ul>\n<li>Plaintext versions of <a href=\"http://lib.store.yahoo.net/lib/paulgraham/acl1.txt\">Chapter 1</a> and <a href=\"http://lib.store.yahoo.net/lib/paulgraham/acl2.txt\">Chapter 2</a> are available online.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Offline Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://weitz.de/cl-recipes/\">Common Lisp Recipes by Edmund Weitz</a> - A great set of Common Lisp patterns.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Offline Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Object-Oriented-Programming-COMMON-LISP-Programmers/dp/0201175894\">Object-Oriented Programming in Common Lisp by Sonya E. Keene</a> - An in-depth description of the CLOS, and shows how to use it with example applications.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Offline Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Art-Metaobject-Protocol-Gregor-Kiczales/dp/0262610744/\">The Art of the Metaobject Protocol by Gregor Kiczales, Jim des Rivieres, and Daniel G. Bobrow</a> - Describes the CLOS Metaobject Protocol (MOP).\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://metamodular.com/CLOS-MOP/\">Chapters 5 and 6 (available online)</a> - The specification of a metaobject protocol extension to CLOS.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.adamtornhill.com/reviews/amop.htm\">Adam Tornhill on AMOP</a> - Recommends reading Practical Common Lisp, then  Object-Oriented Programming in Common Lisp, and then AMOP.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>The <a href=\"http://cliki.net\">Cliki</a> - The Common Lisp Wiki. A great resource for all things CL. Has a great <a href=\"http://cliki.net/Getting+Started\">Getting Started</a> page and an extensive list of <a href=\"http://cliki.net/Lisp%20books\">Lisp books</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.reddit.com/r/lisp/\">Lisp Subreddit</a> - An active community, and has loads of useful links and reference documents in the sidebar.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/Common_Lisp\">Common Lisp Subreddit</a> - The Subreddit for Common Lisp.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Online Community</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://exercism.io/languages/common-lisp/about\">Exercism's Common Lisp track</a> - An excellent way to learn the language through practice, have your code reviewed, and to discuss solutions with other people.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Library Management</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.quicklisp.org/beta\">Quicklisp</a> - A package management platform for Lisp libraries.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Library Management</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://quickdocs.org\">Quickdocs</a> - Documentation for projects in Quicklisp.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Library Management</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://borretti.me/article/common-lisp-sotu-2015\">State of the Common Lisp Ecosystem, 2015</a> - Article about what libraries you should use, and why.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Library Management</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://articulate-lisp.com/project/abcs.html\">Articulate Common Lisp</a> - Lists some useful libraries.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Lisp Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://franz.com/products/allegrocl/\">Allegro Common Lisp (ACL)</a> - Commercial, but has a free <a href=\"https://franz.com/downloads/clp/survey\">Express Edition</a>.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://franz.com/support/documentation/\">ACL manual</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCN36UrxtyNBJPaG0kmBJNRw\">Training videos on YouTube</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Lisp Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cons.org/cmucl/\">Carnegie Mellon University Common Lisp (CMUCL)</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cons.org/cmucl/doc/index.html\">CMUCL manual and other useful information</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Lisp Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://common-lisp.net/project/ecl/\">Embeddable Common Lisp (ECL)</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://common-lisp.net/project/ecl/static/manual/\">ECL manual</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Lisp Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.lispworks.com/products/index.html\">LispWorks</a> - Commercial, but as mentioned previously, has a <a href=\"http://www.lispworks.com/downloads/index.html\">Personal Edition</a> with minor limitations.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.lispworks.com/documentation/index.html\">LispWorks manual</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"GustavBertram/awesome-common-lisp-learning","categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Lisp Implementations</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20171014210404/http://www.scieneer.com/scl/\">Scieneer Common Lisp (SCL)</a> - A commercial Linux and Unix implementation, but has an unrestricted free evaluation and non-commercial use version.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20171014210404/http://www.scieneer.com/scl/doc/\">SCL manual</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T20:18:17.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"webpack-contrib/awesome-webpack","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h4>Component &#x26; Template</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ogonkov/nunjucks-loader\">Simple Nunjucks Loader</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ogonkov/nunjucks-loader\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">16</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":16,\"repo\":\"ogonkov/nunjucks-loader\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Nunjucks template loader. -- <em>Maintainer</em>: <code>ogonkov</code> <a href=\"https://github.com/ogonkov\"><img src=\"https://rawgit.com/d3viant0ne/awesome-webpack/master/media/github-square.svg\" alt=\"Github\"></a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T19:29:49.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"enaqx/awesome-react","categoryHTML":"<h5>React Component Libraries</h5>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/uber/baseweb\">baseweb</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/uber/baseweb\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">6.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":6336,\"repo\":\"uber/baseweb\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Base Web is a foundation for initiating, evolving, and unifying web products.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-01-06T16:27:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"preactjs/awesome-preact","categoryHTML":"<h2>Contents</h2><h3>Example Apps</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://play.cash\"><strong>Play.cash</strong